    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know, i know... that's the standard thing to say. but talking to someone doesn't change the fact that the spark is just dead. it's not a \"mental health\" thing, it's an ontological thing. it's like the pilot has left the plane and now there's just this heavy, useless machine sitting on the runway. how am i supposed to care about \"navigating emotions\" when there's no one left in here to actually feel them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
